Comment: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:17.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=49}PANNING TEXT
Dialogue: 5,0:07:35.18,0:07:38.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Beleza! A toda velocidade!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:38.24,0:07:39.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah! - OG}– Sim!\N– Sim!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:07:39.24,0:07:41.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What's with the solidarity?! - OG}Que solidariedade é essa?!{OG}{How are you all in agreement?! - Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:07:41.14,0:07:44.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Força! Força! Força!\N– Força! Força! Força!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:49.90,0:07:51.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It flew! - OG}Tá voando!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:07:51.80,0:07:55.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't let it get away!\NWe'll move ahead of it and block its course! - OG}Não deixa escapar! Vai na frente\Ne bloqueia o caminho dele!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:55.24,0:07:59.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Força! Força! Força!\N– Força! Força! Força!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:11.89,0:08:13.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We ran ashore on something! - OG}A gente encalhou em alguma coisa!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:16.18,0:08:19.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Ahh... Nami-san, Robin-chan, are you guys okay? - OG}Ah, Nami, Robin, vocês duas estão bem?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:19.39,0:08:21.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Sim, de algum jeito...
Dialogue: 5,0:08:21.99,0:08:23.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu estou bem.
Comment: 5,0:08:24.42,0:08:27.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Good... Hm?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:24.42,0:08:25.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Good... - OG}Ainda bem.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:27.36,0:08:30.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What? What's this sound? - OG}O quê? Que som é esse?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:30.81,0:08:32.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O quê? O que tá acontecendo?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:48.37,0:08:50.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso é...? Não me diga...
Dialogue: 5,0:08:58.35,0:09:00.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why... in a place like this...?! - OG}Por quê...? Num lugar como este...?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:09:00.81,0:09:03.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ai, ai, ai!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:05.55,0:09:08.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Go back! Go back! Turn 180 degrees! - OG}Volta! Volta! Gira 180 graus!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:09:27.25,0:09:29.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Que diabos é isso?!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:32.17,0:09:34.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Wh-Wh-What the hell\Nis this lump of iron?! - OG}Q-Q-Que diabos é esse\Nmonstrão de ferro?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:09:34.80,0:09:36.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Um navio?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:36.26,0:09:39.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No! Something shaped like this can't travel on the sea! - OG}Impossível! Algo com essa forma\Nnão navega no mar!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:09:43.22,0:09:45.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei, sapo! Foge! O que você tá fazendo?!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:53.90,0:09:56.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ah! Ele foi atropelado!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:21.26,0:10:23.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O navio tava soltando fumaça!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:34.38,0:10:35.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Piratas...?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:35.61,0:10:38.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vovó! Vovó! Piratas estão aqui!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:38.36,0:10:41.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What?! Is that true, Chimney?! - OG}O quê?! É verdade, Chimney?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:10:41.74,0:10:45.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá bom, então me traz o Den Den Mushi!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:45.28,0:10:46.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá bom!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:47.00,0:10:50.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso é um problema.\NAlguém saiu do prédio.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:50.12,0:10:52.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eles vão pedir ajuda.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:53.25,0:10:54.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Aqui, Vovó!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:54.69,0:10:56.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hm... Alô?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:56.55,0:11:01.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Let's see... What was it? I forget. - OG}Deixa eu ver... O que era? Esqueci.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:01.21,0:11:02.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So she's drunk?! - OG}Ela tá bêbada?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:07.47,0:11:13.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh? Paille, huh? It goes good with alcohol. - OG}Ah? {\i1}Paille{\i0}, é? Combina com bebida.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:13.08,0:11:15.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Whoa! This is good! - OG}Caramba! Isso é gostoso!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:15.44,0:11:19.20,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,Eu sou a Chimney. Esse é nosso gato, Gonbe,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:19.20,0:11:20.69,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,e a Vovó Kokoro.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:20.69,0:11:24.83,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,Vocês não são assaltantes de trem, são?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:24.83,0:11:27.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu sou o Luffy. Eu sou o homem\Nque vai ser o Rei dos Piratas.{Used as flashback in Enies Lobby 11 @14:51}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:27.70,0:11:28.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Sério?!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:28.42,0:11:29.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:30.00,0:11:31.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Que cara engraçado.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:31.96,0:11:34.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei, Chimney, aquela coisa\Né um navio a vapor, né?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:34.79,0:11:39.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But with a shape like that,\Nit can't go on a voyage. - OG}Mas com aquela forma,\Nnão tem como ele navegar.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:39.03,0:11:41.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You've never seen\Nanything like it, have you? - OG}Nunca viram nada assim, né?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:41.17,0:11:43.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Even if you look all over the world,\Nthis is the only place you can find it. - OG}{You won't find its equal\Nanywhere else in the world. - Z}Esse é o único lugar no mundo onde ele existe.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:43.72,0:11:47.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É um trem marítimo chamado {\i1}Puffing Tom{\i0}.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:47.16,0:11:48.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Puffing Tom{\i0}?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:48.68,0:11:52.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It turns paddlewheels using a steam engine\Nand runs on the sea railway. - OG}{Its steam engine turns paddle wheels\Nwhile it moves along the sea railway. - OG}Um motor a vapor gira as rodas de pás\Nenquanto ele anda na ferrovia marítima.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:55.61,0:11:56.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ferrovia?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:56.79,0:12:00.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's right. It runs a little below\Nthe surface of the sea. - OG}Isso mesmo. Ela flutua\Nlogo abaixo da superfície da água.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:00.19,0:12:05.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O trem viaja a mesma rota todo dia,\Nlevando passageiros de uma ilha a outra.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:05.19,0:12:07.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Também puxa navios e entrega correspondências.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:07.12,0:12:09.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ela tem razão. Realmente tem uma ferrovia.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:09.66,0:12:12.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É! Tem tanto um sinal quanto uma barreira.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:12.50,0:12:14.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's dangerous to come inside like that! - OG}É perigoso atravessar a barreira!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:14.33,0:12:18.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Even if it's dangerous, that guy wouldn't understand, right? - OG}Perigoso ou não,\Naquele cara não entenderia, né?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:18.39,0:12:22.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não foi legal mandar ele voar.\NA gente estava perseguindo ele, sabia?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:22.09,0:12:24.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What? "That guy"?\NAre you talking about Yokozuna? - OG}Por "aquele cara", você quer dizer o Yokozuna?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:24.89,0:12:26.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É, aquele sapo que nada de crawl.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:26.99,0:12:29.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O Yokozuna não morreria com aquilo.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:29.90,0:12:33.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ele é a fonte de todas as nossas\Ndores de cabeça aqui na Shift Station.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:33.09,0:12:36.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He loves strength contests\Nand always tries to defeat the sea train. - OG}Ele adora testar sua força\Ntentando derrotar o trem marítimo.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:36.70,0:12:38.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He'll show up again. - OG}Ele vai voltar.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:38.18,0:12:42.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Strength contests? Oh...\NThat's why he didn't run, huh? - OG}Testar sua força? Ah!\NPor isso ele ficou firme, né?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:42.12,0:12:43.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ele realmente tem coragem.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:43.72,0:12:46.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Give me a break!\NWe're having problems! - OG}Pelo amor! Ele é uma baita dor de cabeça!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:46.37,0:12:49.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The rail guard was broken many times, too! - OG}A grade também vive sendo quebrada!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:49.45,0:12:53.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Every time he shows up,\Nit causes the passengers a lot of trouble! - OG}Toda vez que ele aparece,\Nos passageiros ficam em pânico!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:53.91,0:12:55.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see... - OG}Então é isso que ele faz...{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:55.80,0:12:57.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Okay, then! I'm not gonna eat him! - OG}Beleza, então! Eu {\i1}não{\i0} vou comer ele!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:57.71,0:12:59.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm not gonna eat a fighter! - OG}Eu não posso comer um lutador!{Gaijin: Not enough time for the longer phrasing}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:59.44,0:13:01.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You shouldn't have thought\Nabout eating a frog in the first place! - OG}{Eating a frog should never\Nhave entered your head! - Z}Querer comer ele foi seu primeiro erro!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:01.80,0:13:05.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So where do you guys wanna go? - OG}Então, vocês estão indo pra algum lugar?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.80,0:13:09.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Se vocês forem pegar o trem\Nmarítimo daqui, tem:
Dialogue: 5,0:13:10.70,0:13:16.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,St. Poplar, a Cidade da Rainha da Primavera...\NPucci, a Cidade Gourmet...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:16.14,0:13:18.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,e San Faldo, a Cidade do Carnaval!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:18.86,0:13:20.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,São todos lugares divertidos.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:20.90,0:13:25.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you work for the government,\Nthere's a separate, special train. - OG}Se você trabalha pro governo,\Nvocê pegaria um trem especial separado.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:25.82,0:13:27.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then we'll pick the Gourmet Town. - OG}Beleza, vamos escolher a Cidade Gourmet.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:27.46,0:13:28.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Obviously not! - OG}Claro que não!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:29.60,0:13:32.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Since we've got our own ship,\Nwe won't take the train. - OG}Já que a gente tem nosso próprio navio,\Nnão vamos precisar do trem.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:32.50,0:13:33.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We'll just follow the log. - OG}A gente segue o nosso log.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:33.70,0:13:35.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ah? Pra onde ele tá apontando?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:35.75,0:13:37.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{East of here. - OG}Pro leste daqui.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:37.54,0:13:41.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So I see...\NThen it must be Water Seven. - OG}Entendo... Então deve ser\Nnada menos que Water Seven.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:41.46,0:13:45.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O trem que vocês viram antes veio\Nda Blue Station daquela ilha.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:46.43,0:13:49.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's called the City of Water.\NIt's a nice place. - OG}É chamada de Cidade da Água.\NÉ um lugar muito bom.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:49.14,0:13:53.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Above all, it's a city that made a name\Nfor itself with its shipyard. - OG}Além disso, a cidade é famosa\Npela indústria naval.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:53.15,0:13:55.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Their technology is\NNo. 1 in the world! - OG}A tecnologia deles é a melhor do mundo!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:55.11,0:14:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The ships they build are the World Government's\Nfavorites! Isn't that amazing?! - OG}Até o Governo Mundial prefere\Nos navios construídos lá! Incrível, né?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:00.00,0:14:03.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see... Then there's gotta be \Nsome amazing shipwrights, right?! - OG}Então... eles têm uns carpinteiros\Nnavais incríveis, né?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:03.09,0:14:09.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Not just "some"! It's a hangout\Nfor the world's best shipwrights! - OG}Não só "uns"! Só os melhores\Ncarpinteiros do mundo ficam lá!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:09.49,0:14:10.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Usopp!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:10.54,0:14:11.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:11.80,0:14:13.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Beleza! Eu decidi!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:13.60,0:14:16.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We're gonna go there and get a shipwright\Nto join our crew for sure! - OG}Vamos lá e vamos conseguir um carpinteiro\Npra entrar na tripulação com certeza!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:16.37,0:14:20.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá bem!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:20.36,0:14:22.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll be one heck of an adventure! - OG}Vai ser uma baita aventura!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:22.90,0:14:25.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Sure!}{\q2}Kokoro da Shift Station aqui.\NHá algo que eu gostaria de pedir.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:23.88,0:14:25.17,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,Então você já ligou.\NTava na hora de vocês virem aqui.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:25.17,0:14:30.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Isn't that convenient? - OG}Não é conveniente?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:30.29,0:14:35.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Let's take the sea train that arrives this evening\Nand go to Water Seven! - OG}Vamos pegar o trem marítimo que chega\Nhoje à noite e ir pra Water Seven!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:35.60,0:14:38.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What?! Really?!\NDoes the sea train stop here?! - OG}O quê?! Sério?!\NO trem marítimo para aqui?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:38.94,0:14:40.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É claro que para!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:40.13,0:14:42.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Essa é a Shift Station, sabia?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:47.39,0:14:50.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Uhuuu!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:50.91,0:14:56.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vovó! Vovó!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:57.58,0:15:00.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O Sea Train chegou!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:00.17,0:15:05.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O Sea Train está chegando!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:06.26,0:15:08.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Uaau! Incrível!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:09.80,0:15:13.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá vindo! Tá vindo!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:13.40,0:15:14.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The sea train! - OG}É o trem marítimo!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:15:14.18,0:15:15.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É enorme!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:15.20,0:15:18.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That frog!\NIs it trying to take on the sea train again?! - OG}Aquele sapo!\NEle tá tentando enfrentar o trem de novo?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:15:24.80,0:15:26.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ele tá lá!\NÓ aquele idiota sentado no trilho!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:28.82,0:15:32.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Even if it's Yokozuna, it's dangerous\Nto challenge the Puffing Tom! - OG}Mesmo sendo o Yokozuna, é perigoso\Ndesafiar o Puffing Tom!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:15:32.03,0:15:34.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O sapo não devia desistir?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:34.95,0:15:37.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Please don't die, Yokozuna! - OG}Por favor, não morre, Yokozuna!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:37.62,0:15:39.58,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Ele desafiou o trem?!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:49.04,0:15:51.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Lá vem! Vai embora!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:51.69,0:15:54.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vai, Yokozuna!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:54.50,0:15:55.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{– Yay!\N– Yay! - OG}– Vai!\N– Vai!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:15:56.31,0:16:01.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yokozuna!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:01.26,0:16:03.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Whew! He swerved at the last minute! - OG}Ufa! Ele desviou no último segundo!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:03.21,0:16:06.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yokozuna, hoje foi de boa! Tá inteiro!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:06.90,0:16:11.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Those two are close, aren't they? - OG}Esses dois são próximos, né?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:11.49,0:16:14.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Chimney grew up watching\NMr. Yokozuna's fighting spirit. - OG}A Chimney cresceu vendo\No espírito de luta do Sr. Yokozuna.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:14.09,0:16:18.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O trem tá parando!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:18.49,0:16:22.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Legal!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:22.33,0:16:26.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is this the sea train?! - OG}Esse é o trem marítimo?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:26.34,0:16:30.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Sea trains are amazing! - OG}Trens marítimos são incríveis!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:31.47,0:16:32.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É tão grande!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:32.38,0:16:34.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:35.01,0:16:36.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É o Puffing Tom!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:36.51,0:16:39.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Quem fez isso?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:40.35,0:16:42.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I did! And its name isn't "Puffing Tom." - OG}Eu fiz! E o nome dele não é "Puffing Tom".{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:42.09,0:16:45.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I named it "Rocketman." - OG}Eu nomeei ele de "Rocketman".{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:45.68,0:16:49.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Rocketman?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:49.41,0:16:51.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But they went and named it\N"Puffing Tom" without my permission. - OG}Mas eles foram lá e nomearam\Nde "Puffing Tom" sem minha permissão.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:51.24,0:16:52.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm the one who designed\Nand built this ship! - OG}Eu é que projetei\Ne construí esse navio!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:52.70,0:16:55.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu sabia.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:55.87,0:16:57.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The one who made the sea train\Nis your acquaintance, huh? - OG}O cara que fez o trem\Nmarítimo é seu conhecido, é?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:16:57.52,0:16:59.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É, ele também era carpinteiro naval.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:59.24,0:17:01.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He built the sea train\Nand saved this island. - OG}Ele construiu o trem marítimo\Ne salvou essa ilha.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:01.75,0:17:05.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He was a genius shipwright. - OG}Ele era um carpinteiro naval genial.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:15.78,0:17:17.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You mean "was"? What happened to him? - OG}Você disse "era"? O que aconteceu com ele?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:17.60,0:17:22.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well... that's a... story for another day. - OG}Bom... isso é... uma história pra outro dia.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:22.89,0:17:27.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei, o trem tá indo embora!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:27.81,0:17:29.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In any case, for the time being,\Nyou'll have to switch ships at Water Seven. - OG}{For the time being, your immediate destination is Water Seven. - Z}Por enquanto, seu destino imediato é Water Seven.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:29.27,0:17:29.65,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{You should think about what\Nyou'll do going forward. - OG}Vocês deviam pensar no que\Nvão fazer daqui pra frente.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:29.65,0:17:34.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Beleza!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:34.86,0:17:38.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Here! Here!\NI'll write a letter of introduction! - OG}Aqui! Aqui!\NVou escrever uma carta de apresentação!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:38.41,0:17:41.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{When you go to Water Seven, take this letter to a man named Iceburg. - OG}Quando chegarem em Water Seven,\Nlevem essa carta pra um homem chamado Iceburg.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:41.95,0:17:44.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He'll fix your ship in no time! - OG}Ele conserta o navio de vocês num instante!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:44.95,0:17:48.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is he a shipwright? - OG}Ele é carpinteiro naval?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:49.26,0:17:50.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Just take the letter to him! - OG}Só leva a carta pra ele!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:50.90,0:17:52.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Here. Don't lose it. - OG}Aqui. Não perde.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:53.26,0:17:54.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Obrigado, vovó!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:54.89,0:17:55.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh, it's nothing.\NYou kids shouldn't be so formal. - OG}Ah, não é nada.\NVocês não precisam ser tão formais.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:57.93,0:18:01.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vovó! Tô aqui!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:02.81,0:18:05.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei! Chimney, vem com a gente!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:05.09,0:18:08.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:18.28,0:18:19.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why not? - OG}Por quê?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:18:21.70,0:18:22.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tchau-tchau!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:28.01,0:18:30.37,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,Tchau, Chimney! Gonbe!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:39.59,0:18:41.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tchau!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:42.90,0:18:45.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It should take about a day\Nto get to Water Seven. - OG}Deve levar mais ou menos um dia\Npra chegar em Water Seven.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:18:45.72,0:18:47.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why don't you sleep for the night? - OG}Por que não dormem essa noite?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:18:47.43,0:18:49.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Boa ideia.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:50.41,0:18:52.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Boa noite, Luffy!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:54.13,0:18:55.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Boa noite!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:55.61,0:18:56.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Boa noite, Usopp!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:57.69,0:19:00.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Boa noite!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:59.61,0:19:00.20,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{Zoro, you sleep too much. - OG}Zoro, você dorme demais.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:00.20,0:19:03.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see we're making good headway. - OG}Parece que estamos avançando bem.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:03.60,0:19:05.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Amanhã chegaremos ao nosso destino.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:06.81,0:19:09.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Estou ansiosa pra ver\Nque tipo de cidade é.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:14.75,0:19:17.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin, não vai dormir?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:17.71,0:19:21.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I will. In a bit. - OG}Vou. Daqui a pouco.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:29.94,0:19:34.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Boa noite!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:34.94,0:19:36.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Boa noite.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:36.27,0:19:39.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Have you been to\NWater Seven before? - OG}Você já foi pra\NWater Seven antes?{Z}
Comment: 5,0:19:39.24,0:19:39.86,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{Huh? - OG}Hm?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:39.86,0:19:42.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não. Esta é a primeira vez.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:43.09,0:19:45.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Estou vendo!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:45.53,0:19:48.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Estou vendo! Estou vendo!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:49.20,0:19:51.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É uma cidade enorme!
Comment: 5,0:19:53.01,0:19:54.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:54.00,0:19:57.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Caramba! Que cidade enorme!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:57.92,0:20:00.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso é uma cachoeira!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:00.45,0:20:03.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Essa é Water Seven?!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:03.08,0:20:05.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Incrível!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:05.39,0:20:10.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É linda!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:10.38,0:20:11.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Então é essa a famosa Water Seven!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:11.98,0:20:13.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see. So the island as a whole is\Nshaped like a fountain. - OG}Entendo. Então a ilha toda tem\Nformato de fonte.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:13.50,0:20:14.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Olha!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:14.81,0:20:17.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What the hell?! There's a frog\Nhere, too?! - OG}Que isso?! Tem um sapo\Naqui também?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:19.54,0:20:21.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The current at the entrance\Nis surprisingly strong! - OG}A corrente na entrada\Né surpreendentemente forte!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:21.60,0:20:25.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In any case, it looks like\Nwe can ride the current up! - OG}De qualquer forma, parece que\Na gente pode subir na corrente!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:25.21,0:20:27.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vai ser como um parque aquático!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:35.10,0:20:36.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Segurem firme, galera!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:36.75,0:20:39.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Lá vamos nós!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:42.92,0:20:47.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Uhuuuu!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:48.80,0:20:52.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Uau!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:52.35,0:20:55.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Incrível!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:55.62,0:20:58.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso é demais!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:58.11,0:21:03.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A cidade é enorme!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:03.34,0:21:06.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm going to look for a currency exchange\Nand a place to stock up on food. - OG}Eu vou procurar uma casa de câmbio\Ne um lugar pra reabastecer comida.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:06.78,0:21:10.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So we can sell that stuff? - OG}Então a gente pode vender aquelas coisas?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:10.36,0:21:12.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Gold. The gold we brought back from Skypiea. - OG}Ouro. O ouro que trouxemos de Skypiea.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:12.79,0:21:14.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see! If we sell gold, we'd\Nmake loads of money, right?! - OG}É mesmo! Se vendermos ouro,\Na gente faz uma grana enorme, né?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:14.12,0:21:15.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{While I'm doing that, you guys\Nwill go to the shipyard. - OG}Enquanto eu faço isso, vocês\Nvão ao estaleiro.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:15.68,0:21:17.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What're we going there for? - OG}Pra que a gente vai lá?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:19.04,0:21:21.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To get the ship repaired, obviously. - OG}Pra consertar o navio, obviamente.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:21.39,0:21:22.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Espera, Nami!\NVocê não disse que ia comigo?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:24.01,0:21:25.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá tudo bem.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:25.10,0:21:29.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A Nami cuida melhor do dinheiro\Ndo que qualquer um de nós.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:29.97,0:21:33.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Robin! You can't carry\Nheavy things yet. - OG}Robin! Você ainda não pode\Ncarregar coisas pesadas.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:33.70,0:21:37.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu sei. Eu ia fazer compras leves.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:37.06,0:21:42.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É... nem pensar!\NNão com a sua condição!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:42.57,0:21:44.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 5,0:21:44.69,0:21:45.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá bom.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:47.20,0:21:50.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Nesse caso, Chopper vai com a Robin.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:50.36,0:21:51.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Cuida dela, Chopper.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:51.87,0:21:54.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Pode deixar!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:55.54,0:21:58.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá bom. Luffy, fica com essa metade.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:58.07,0:22:00.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu fico com a outra metade.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:03.51,0:22:06.20,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,{Don't you dare lose it, okay? - OG}Não perde isso por nada, tá?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:22:06.20,0:22:09.31,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,{Make sure that you hand it to the shipwrights\Nand negotiate the repair cost! - OG}Entrega pros carpinteiros\Ne negocia o custo do conserto!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:22:09.31,0:22:12.30,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,Beleza!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:12.30,0:22:16.96,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,{I can't believe she's\Ntrusting this to Luffy. - OG}Não acredito que ela\Ntá confiando isso no Luffy.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:22:17.80,0:22:20.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bom, Usopp, cuida do navio.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:20.36,0:22:25.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Pode deixar.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:26.80,0:22:29.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Beleza, vamos!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:31.24,0:22:33.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Let's take the yagara. - OG}Vamos pegar o yagara.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:22:44.71,0:22:47.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yagara? Aquele bicho que parece cavalo?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:47.60,0:22:50.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What?! We get to ride a yagara?! - OG}O quê?! A gente vai andar num yagara?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:22:50.68,0:22:53.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Like we have a choice. - OG}Como se tivéssemos outra opção.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:22:54.14,0:22:56.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This town's canals are\Nits main transportation routes. - OG}Os canais dessa cidade são\Nas principais rotas de transporte.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:22:56.60,0:22:59.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Legal!
Dialogue: 5,0:23:10.54,0:23:14.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see. There's a rental\Nstation for yagaras! - OG}Entendi. Tem uma estação\Nde aluguel de yagaras!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:23:25.56,0:23:27.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How many would you like? - OG}Quantos gostariam?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:23:27.46,0:23:29.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Three, please. - OG}Três, por favor.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:23:30.27,0:23:31.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu quero um também!
Dialogue: 5,0:23:31.43,0:23:36.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why?! You're staying here! - OG}Pra quê?! Você vai ficar aqui!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:23:38.48,0:23:40.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Two yagara bulls and\None yagara calf, was it? - OG}Dois touros yagara e\Num bezerro yagara, certo?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:23:40.44,0:23:45.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh? They have young ones too? - OG}Ah? Eles também têm filhotes?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:23:55.16,0:23:58.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eles são bonitinhos!
Dialogue: 5,0:23:58.79,0:24:00.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso é demais!
Dialogue: 5,0:24:03.46,0:24:07.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Então, como você direciona eles?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:07.91,0:24:10.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yagaras são bem inteligentes.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:23.50,0:24:25.50,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,{They understand human language,\Nso just tell them where you want to go! - OG}Eles entendem a linguagem humana,\Nentão é só dizer pra onde quer ir!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:24:25.50,0:24:28.86,Main-207+,,0,0,12,,Só isso?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:30.30,0:24:32.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Plus, they know the city inside and out,\Nso they won't get lost! - OG}Além disso, eles conhecem a cidade de cor,\Nentão não se perdem!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:24:32.61,0:24:35.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Que conveniente!
Dialogue: 5,0:24:35.17,0:24:40.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{My recommendation would be to\Nsplit into the following groups: - OG}Eu recomendo que\Nse dividam nos seguintes grupos:{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:24:40.70,0:24:43.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The two of you on one yagara bull. - OG}Vocês duas num touro yagara.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:24:43.16,0:24:46.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The two of you on another yagara bull. - OG}Vocês dois em outro touro yagara.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:24:46.83,0:24:48.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And one of you on a yagara calf. - OG}E um de vocês num bezerro yagara.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:24:48.73,0:24:50.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eu vou nesse!
Dialogue: 5,0:24:50.38,0:24:54.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Luffy gets the calf?! - OG}O Luffy fica com o filhote?!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:24:54.72,0:24:57.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É, porque se eu ficar sozinho,\Nposso ir pra qualquer lugar!
Dialogue: 5,0:24:57.68,0:25:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Will you be okay by yourself? - OG}Você vai ficar bem sozinho?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:00.00,0:25:02.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Deixa comigo!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:02.51,0:25:04.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Please be back by five o'clock. - OG}Por favor, voltem até as cinco horas.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:04.73,0:25:07.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Enjoy your sightseeing of Water Seven! - OG}Aproveitem o passeio por Water Seven!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:07.61,0:25:08.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vamos, vamos!
Comment: 5,0:25:08.36,0:25:11.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ah... Ahh... Ahh... That really hurts!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:09.57,0:25:13.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei! Yagara, pra onde fica o estaleiro?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:13.53,0:25:14.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A direção oposta daquela garota.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:14.90,0:25:18.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Let's go to the shopping district first! - OG}Vamos pro distrito comercial primeiro!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:19.49,0:25:21.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey, we should go to the shipyard first! - OG}Ei, a gente devia ir pro estaleiro primeiro!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:21.05,0:25:22.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You can use them anywhere in town, Miss. - OG}Pode usá-los em qualquer lugar da cidade, moça.{Z}
Comment: 0,0:25:22.12,0:25:22.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=52}START BULL
Dialogue: 5,0:25:22.12,0:25:24.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But the yagara calf can only\Nbe used on the back streets. - OG}Mas o bezerro yagara só pode\Nser usado nas ruas de trás.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:24.00,0:25:24.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The back streets? - OG}As ruas de trás?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:24.04,0:25:24.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yes. They're small waterways,\Nso only small yagaras can fit in. - OG}Sim. São canais pequenos,\Nentão só yagaras pequenos cabem.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:24.09,0:25:24.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I see. Nami and I will part ways, then. - OG}Entendo. Então a Nami e eu nos separamos aqui.{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:24.13,0:25:24.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Luffy, I'm counting on you\Nfor the ship's repair, okay? - OG}Luffy, tô contando com você\Npro conserto do navio, tá?{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:24.17,0:25:24.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Pode deixar comigo!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:24.21,0:25:24.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Podemos ir?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:24.25,0:25:24.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Beleza! Vai, yagara!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:24.34,0:25:25.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Obrigado pela preferência! Cuidado!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:25.38,0:25:25.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Dash to the shipyard! - OG}A toda velocidade pro estaleiro!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:25.42,0:25:25.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:25.46,0:25:25.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que é um "touro"?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:25.50,0:25:25.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que é um "touro"?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:25.55,0:25:25.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que é um "touro"?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:25.59,0:25:25.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O que é um "touro"?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:25.71,0:25:27.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Sei lá. Bulldogs?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:28.72,0:25:30.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não pode ser, né?
Comment: 0,0:25:22.12,0:25:22.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=53}END BULL
Dialogue: 5,0:25:30.00,0:25:32.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Com licença! Gostaríamos de alugar uns touros!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:32.52,0:25:34.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Pergunta primeiro o que eles são!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:35.42,0:25:38.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bem-vindos! Vieram alugar touros,\Ncerto? Pra quantas pessoas?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:38.39,0:25:39.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Três!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:39.51,0:25:41.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Que tipo de touros gostariam?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:41.50,0:25:44.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Existem três classes:\Nyagara, rabuka e king.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:44.18,0:25:47.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bom, pra vocês três,\Ndois yagaras devem servir.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:47.32,0:25:49.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Beleza, assa eles bem gostoso!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:49.15,0:25:50.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Não fala besteira, seu esquisito!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:51.70,0:25:54.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ah? O log pose de vocês trouxe vocês aqui?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:54.44,0:25:55.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isso.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:55.16,0:25:57.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Que aventura, hein, vocês.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:57.39,0:25:59.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Então vocês não faziam ideia\Ndo que eram os touros, né?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:59.70,0:26:00.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Isso.\N– Isso.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:00.75,0:26:03.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bom, resumindo, aqueles são os touros.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:03.29,0:26:05.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Touros yagara. Vocês vão ver eles por toda a cidade.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:05.96,0:26:10.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Nessa região, tem um peixe chamado yagara\Nque nada com a cabeça pra fora.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:10.24,0:26:13.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Essa é a Cidade da Água.\NTem mais canais do que passarelas.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:13.96,0:26:17.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Os moradores daqui veem os touros\Ncomo um transporte essencial.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:18.30,0:26:20.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,O mesmo vale pra qualquer passeio na ilha.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:20.76,0:26:22.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Aquele peixe tá puxando um barco?
Dialogue: 5,0:26:22.82,0:26:25.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Na verdade, eles deixam as pessoas montarem neles.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:25.43,0:26:29.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bom, é tipo andar a cavalo\Nou de carruagem em terra firme.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:29.65,0:26:31.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vamos lá!
Dialogue: 5,0:26:31.61,0:26:35.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá vendo o cercado de peixes ali?\NBom, tenta montar em um. É confortável.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:36.40,0:26:40.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Pra dois touros yagara de dois passageiros,\Nvai ser 2.000 belly no total.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:40.26,0:26:41.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Uau, eles são fofinhos!
Dialogue: 5,0:26:41.74,0:26:44.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É um peixe que parece um cavalo.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:45.66,0:26:49.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Seu idiota! Por que fez isso?!
Dialogue: 5,0:26:49.50,0:26:52.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ah? Ele deve ter gostado de você.\NVamos pegar esse pra você.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:59.18,0:27:01.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ele aguenta carregar coisas pesadas?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:01.39,0:27:05.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,A força deles é incrível! São muito usados\Npra mudanças de casa.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:05.95,0:27:08.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Que bolsa, hein? O que tem aí dentro?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:08.25,0:27:09.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ouro.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:10.29,0:27:13.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Boa! Seja o que for, eles aguentam.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:13.23,0:27:13.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tá vendo?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:13.86,0:27:16.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Uau! Me dá!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:15.04,0:27:16.04,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,Nem pensar!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:16.04,0:27:18.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Esse cara é sincero demais.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:18.03,0:27:20.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,E você! Não fica mostrando isso\Npros outros assim!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:20.70,0:27:22.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Por quê? Não é nada demais.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:22.69,0:27:24.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Minha... Que surpresa.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:24.74,0:27:28.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bom, então... Vai ser um milhão de berry\Npra dois touros yagara.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:28.72,0:27:30.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ei, o preço subiu, moço.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:30.58,0:27:33.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ah, é verdade, tem alguma casa\Nde câmbio por aqui?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:33.33,0:27:40.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Tem, mas com essa quantidade de ouro,\Nas lojas daqui provavelmente não vão ter dinheiro suficiente.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:40.40,0:27:42.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Você deveria ir ao centro na Ilha do Estaleiro.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:42.89,0:27:46.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Centro da Ilha do Estaleiro? Onde fica?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:46.72,0:27:50.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Naquela direção. Leva isso com você.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:50.00,0:27:51.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Um mapa?! Aha!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:52.01,0:27:53.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vai ajudar muito! Obrigado!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:53.44,0:27:56.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Moço, o estaleiro é pra aquele lado também?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:56.38,0:27:58.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É. O estaleiro número um do mundo!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:58.81,0:28:02.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Perfeito! Quando pegarmos o dinheiro,\Na gente vai estar pertinho do estaleiro.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:02.95,0:28:06.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,É. Finalmente podemos consertar\No Going Merry!
Dialogue: 5,0:28:06.74,0:28:10.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,E vamos encontrar um carpinteiro também!\NTô ficando empolgado!
Dialogue: 5,0:28:10.54,0:28:11.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bom, então...
Dialogue: 5,0:28:11.59,0:28:12.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vamos?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:12.46,0:28:15.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Beleza! Vai, yagara!
Dialogue: 5,0:28:17.30,0:28:20.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Obrigado pela preferência! Cuidado!
Dialogue: 5,0:28:20.63,0:28:23.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Dash to the shipyard! - OG}A toda velocidade pro estaleiro!{Z}
Dialogue: 5,0:28:23.73,0:28:26.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=19=57}===============================DIALOGUE============================
